abstract: Karen Crouse On Golf column observes that golfers and fans alike were overcome with compassion as Tiger Woods stumbled through the worst round of his professional career, an 82 at Phoenix Open golf tournament.
lead_paragraph: Fans expressed pity as Tiger Woods stumbled through the worst round of his professional career, an 82 at the Phoenix Open. At 23 strokes back after 36 holes, he missed the cut.
